14.explanation: Visible spectroscopy of C-type asteroids; unrelated to Psyche's M-class composition or JWST data.

16.explanation: Isotopic study of core formation; unrelated to surface hydration or JWST spectroscopy.

strengths: Multiple highly relevant results (1,2,4,10) directly addressing Psyche's hydration with JWST data
Good contextual papers (3,6,8) providing background on M-class hydration
Broad coverage of hydration detection methodologies across the asteroid belt
weaknesses: Significant redundancy in top results (1,2,10 appear to be duplicates)
Many results (5,7,9,11-20) focus on unrelated targets/methods
Limited diversity in novel approaches beyond JWST 3μm analysis
suggestions: Prioritize unique studies with complementary methodologies (e.g., laboratory comparisons)
Include more recent work on exogenous vs endogenous hydration mechanisms
Expand search to include dynamical modeling of Psyche's potential migration
